<DOC><DOCNO> AP890611-0041 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-11-89 1552EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Burma-Rebels     06-11 0162</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Burma-Rebels,0167</SECOND><HEAD>Burmese Troops Attack Ethnic Rebels</HEAD><DATELINE>MAE SOT, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   About 1,500 Burmese troops attacked astronghold of ethnic Karen rebels near the Thai on border Sunday,Thai border police reported.   They said about 700 Karen guerrillas were defending the Pa Loobase and about 2,000 civilians had fled the area.   Burmese forces began pounding the camp with hundreds of shellsand bombs early Sunday, said the police, who spoke on condition ofanonymity.   There were no immediate casualty reports from Sunday's fighting,which was still heavy late in the day.   However, Karen sources said 22 Burmese soldiers and six rebelshad been killed since battles began around the camp on June 1. Theysaid 31 government troops were wounded along with 13 Karens.   Karens are the largest of a dozen ethnic rebel groups which havebattled for 40 years seeking more autonomy from the centralgovernment. Authorities opened an intensive campaign last October tocrush the Karen insurgency.</TEXT></DOC>